com.MASTAdView
Class MASTAdLog

java.lang.Object
  com.MASTAdView.MASTAdLog

public final class MASTAdLog
extends java.lang.Object

The SDK is instrumented with log() calls to record errors, warnings and server traffic for diagnostic purposes. A small buffer of log events are kept in a memory buffer, and events are also sent to the system log (accessible with the logcat interface.) When reporting problem it is helpful to capture this diagnostic information to aid with debugging and resolution.

setLogLevel

public void setLogLevel(int logLevel)
Set log level to one of the log level values defined in he MASTAdLog class (corresponding to errors, errors + warnings, or everything including server traffic.) The SDK is instrumented with diagnostics logging that can assist with troubleshooting integration problems. Log messages are sent to the system logging interface (viewable with logcat) and an in-memory log of recent messages is stored for easy access.

Parameters:
logLevel - Int log level to control which messages will be sent to the logs.
See Also:
See the MASTAdLog class for more information about logging.
